Founded as a spin-off from CNRS lab Institut Langevin, OWLO is building next generation microscopy for healthcare. 
 
 Our unique technology is the first to provide real-time 3D imaging in a non invasive way. Powered by AI image analysis, this innovation will change research and medical practice by making visible and quantifying what was previously unseen.
 
 Our first use case is in Assisted Reproductive Technologies (ART) where 75% of embryos transfers fail today, resulting in long and expensive procedures that are very stressful and demanding for women. We provide an entirely new way of looking at embryos with new indicators to predict their viability before implantation to improve the efficiency of the procedure and reduce its cost.

column5: Our geochemistry laboratory is a leading specialist in the field of hydrothermal alteration and hydrogen-optimized production from rocks. Together, let's become players in the production of natural H2, for a new low-carbon energy mix.
column7: My research focuses on processes that help to optimize hydrogen production in ultrabasic reservoirs. This is based on experimental approaches to rock alteration and oxidation processes, such as serpentinization. My main interests are in quantifying hydrogen production and consumption, and COâ‚‚ storage by mineralization. My experiments allow me to analyze the entire system and compare the initial and final mineral assemblies. Thus, the production of Hâ‚‚ as a function of the different tested parameters can be compared. I am currently working on developing an experimental geochemistry start-up called RockyH2. This is based on the work of my former thesis supervisors, Pr. Muriel Andreani and Dr. Eric C Gaucher (who are also the founders), as well as my own work. RockyH2 aims to become a major player in the sector of optimized/stimulated production of natural hydrogen from rocks or materials, alongside synchronous COâ‚‚ storage under mineral or reduced forms. Positioned at the interface between academia and industry, this initiative will develop innovative engineering, chemical and physical solutions to optimize and stimulate hydrogen production.

column7: â˜€ï¸â˜€ï¸â˜€ï¸ SEPTEMBER 21st - SUNDAY DAY OF ACTION â˜€ï¸â˜€ï¸â˜€ï¸ ECAN (the Employee Climate Action Network) is an official partner of Sun Day, celebrating the power of renewable energy. Credit for the background image: @mikehankin." -------------- Hello, I'm Laure. I'm a full time climate activist. It's ok, don't get scared ! My purpose is to guide and empower people who work on the inside of large companies to find meaningful ways to take climate action through the lens of their job - no matter what this job is. I do this because: â¤ Climate change is the defining challenge of our time â¤ We need to act like the cavalry is not coming. We cannot afford to wait for someone else to solve this for us. I am someone else. â¤ I want to be able to tell my children that I showed up and did everything I could On this platform, I share my personal views on how and why (most) companies are falling short of what is required to address the climate crisis - and what can be done about it. I call out greenwashing, but I don't want to throw anyone under the bus. This is about finding ways to do better, and most importantly, do what is required (aka, aligned with the science) I am always up for a chat (but no cold outreach about your latest solution on how AI agents will 10x my business please!) You can reach me at laure.legros@workforclimate.org
